OL,6,F"I'm satisfied that somebody ... who
OL,7,Fchooses not to tell that other person
OL,8,Fthey are carrying a condition such as
OL,9,FHIV, who chooses to ignore advice
OL,10,Fabout informing partners ... does so,
OL,11,Fin my view, with a significant degree
OL,12,Fof premeditation.
OL,14,F"There are consequences (the victim)
OL,15,Fhas to be aware of managing that, and
OL,16,Fshe lives with the constant threat
OL,17,Fthat that virus could prove really
OL,18,Fquite serious indeed... to the point
OL,19,Fof being fatal."
